&lt;h1 id="laundry"&gt;Laundry&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Version 1.0&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;October 2004&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As E. B. White said, &amp;ldquo;good writing is rewriting.&amp;rdquo; I didn&amp;rsquo;t realize this when I was in school. In writing, as in math and science, they only show you the finished product. You don&amp;rsquo;t see all the false starts. This gives students a misleading view of how things get made.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The Age of the Essay</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/essay/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/essay/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/essay/"&gt;Chinese Version&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
